e price discrepancy in government-bond markets.=E2=80=9D</p> <p style=3D"ma=
rgin: 16px 0;">(Why do you want to buy Treasury futures and not Treasury bo=
nds=3F Various reasons, with a standard one being that you are an asset man=
ager who is not supposed to borrow a lot of money yourself. You have $1 mil=
lion to spend, and you want to spend it on corporate credit, so you buy cor=
porate bonds. But you also want more exposure to long-term interest rates, =
so you buy Treasury futures from me, which gives you $1 million of rates ex=
posure but which doesn=E2=80=99t require you=C2=A0to pay me any money now.<=
a href=3D"#footnote-4" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !impo=
